I"í<p>In crypto, <strong>LTH</strong> stands either for ‚ÄúLong-Term Holding‚Äù or ‚ÄúLong-Term Holder‚Äù.</p>

<p>A person who is a ‚ÄúLong-Term Holder‚Äù is someone who invested in cryptocurrencies for at least several years. LTH is not a short-term market speculation, but a long-term bullish opinion on a cryptocurrency or blockchain in general.</p>

<h4 id="lth-and-dca">LTH and DCA</h4>

<p>Very often, ‚ÄúLong-Term Holder‚Äù will practice the <a href="/strategy/dollar-cost-averaging/">strategy of DCA</a>, or dollar cost averaging, to purchase cryptocurrency. This is done to avoid any speculation at whatsoever.</p>

<p>Often the purchasing process is automated as well, to minimize psychological impact that might come with the price volatility of cryptocurrencies.</p>

<p>The most popular crypto wallet among LTHs is the Ledger wallet.</p>

